commText: SRH as expected make their impact sub - Head in and and Natarajan out. Expect fireworks from ball one. Jacks to start off. From round the wicket.
Welcome back. RCB in a huddle. Kohli presents the cap to Swapnil Singh. A few words as well.
-- Just a solitary over for Bhuvneshwar Kumar today - the only other time he bowled as few in an uninterrupted IPL match was way back in 2012.
SRH bowlers today \nLeft-arm bowlers: 5/93 in 12 overs (ER 7.75) \nRight-arm bowlers: 2/111 in 8 overs (ER 13.87)
Most consecutive 200+ totals by a team in IPL 4 Punjab Kings in 2023 3 Kolkata Knight Riders in 2023 3 Sunrisers Hyderabad in 2023-24 3* Royal Challengers Bengaluru in 2024

Rajat Patidar: I think the surface is double-paced, especially for fast bowlers. We can use cutters well on this wicket. The spinners will try to bowl back of a length as much as possible. I was just planning my innings, I was not thinking about century. (4 consecutive sixes vs Markande) It was not a plan but I started well in that over, I was trying to maximise. Playing spinners, I try to maximise. to take as many runs in an over as I can, to keep the pressure on the bowler. I was trying to maximise the fast bowler as well, but I'll try in the next match. (Advice to the bowlers) We should use good slower balls on this wicket.

21:10 Local Time, 15:40 GMT, 21:10 IST: SRH will be happy with this score. Not often you say that when their opponents make 206. But such is SRH's batting might this season. Faf and Kohli started well in the powerplay before T Natarajan got the former. Kohli slowed down after the powerplay and was content on nudging and nurdling around. But Patidar took the pressure off him with a 19-ball 50. He hit four consecutive sixes off Markande and he fell at the wrong time for RCB. Green came in and played an useful hand even as Kohli fell after the 2nd strategic timeout, in an attempt to up the rate. Unadkat was the pick of the bowlers for SRH with his slower ball off-cutters doing the damage. T Natarajan too was good as he again kept it tight. At this stage, SRH are favorites. Back for the chase in 5 minutes...

T Natarajan to Swapnil Singh, out Caught by Abhishek Sharma!! A low full-toss on off, Swapnil Singh lofts and finds long-off. Abhishek runs in to take a simple catch. Good last over after the first two balls. Swapnil Singh c Abhishek Sharma b T Natarajan 12(6) [4s-1 6s-1]
T Natarajan to Swapnil Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
T Natarajan to Green, 1 run, full outside off, drilled hard and straight to long-off and it's just one
T Natarajan to Swapnil Singh, 1 run, a low full-toss outside off, Swapnil Singh shuffles across to scoop and does not get it, in the air but on the bounce to short fine-leg

T Natarajan to Swapnil Singh, no run, slower ball off-cutter dug in, Swapnil Singh pulls and misses, Swapnil wants to know the height on that, has reviewed this. Cummins has a chat with T Natarajan meanwhile, about the field. Swapnil is up in the air but the third ump does not feel that it would have gone over the head of the batter, fair delivery
Cummins setting his field. A sweeper cover just the man back on the off-side.
T Natarajan to Swapnil Singh, FOUR, full and wide outside off, Swapnil Singh throws the bat and the thick outside-edge flies over backward point and the off-side field is up
T Natarajan to Swapnil Singh, SIX, the sub makes an impact. A low full-toss on the stumps, heaved into the deep mid-wicket stands, powerful blow
Today was the sixth instance of Pat Cummins conceding 50+ runs in an IPL match - the most by any overseas bowler and joint second most among all bowlers behind Mohit Sharma's seven
Cummins to Swapnil Singh, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter on off, helped down to deep square leg
Swapnil Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
RCB have made their impact sub - Patidar out, Swapnil Singh in.

Cummins to Karthik, out Caught by Abdul Samad!! Finally a wicket for Cummins. The slower ball off-cutter dug in on off, Karthik miscues the pull, Samad initially at deep square leg did not pick that, but ran in and completed a fairly easy catch. End of the dangerous Karthik. Karthik c Abdul Samad b Cummins 11(6) [4s-2]
Cummins to Karthik, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Cummins to Karthik, wide, slower ball off-cutter dug in but it's wide down leg, left alone and wide taken
Cummins to Karthik, FOUR, smashed straight down the ground. Cummins misses the yorker and it's a half-volley outside off, Karthik hammers it wide of mid-on
Cummins to Green, 1 run, full on the stumps, drilled to long-off, on the bounce
Cummins to Green, FOUR, more good batting. A slower ball off-cutter dug in, Green makes room and flat-bats over extra-cover and again excellent placement

Cummins to Green, FOUR, beautiful delivery but what a shot. A low full-toss on the stumps, Green makes room and drills it straight down the ground and gives long-off or long-on no chance, not far from the yorker length but Green got under it
Pat Cummins [3.0-0-40-0] is back into the attack

Best figures in 100th IPL game 4/11 Amit Mishra DC v PK 2016 3/15 Harshal Patel PK vs GT 2024 3/22 R Jadeja CSK vs PK 2015 3/27 Harbhajan MI vs RCB 2015 3/30 J Unadkat SRH vs RCB 2024 3/36 Mohit Sharma GT vs CSK 2023
T Natarajan to Karthik, FOUR, did not go for the yorker and is put away. A slower ball off-cutter outside off, Karthik gets forward and slams the lofted drive wide of extra-cover
The off-side field is up.
T Natarajan to Karthik, 2 runs, full and angling into leg-stump, Karthik heaves wide of deep mid-wicket and it's just two
T Natarajan round the wicket.
T Natarajan to Green, 1 run, full on the stumps, drilled on the bounce to Samad at long-on
T Natarajan to Green, wide, the wide yorker is wide of the tramline on the off-side, left alone
T Natarajan to Green, 2 runs, slower ball off-cutter outside off, Green cuts wide of sweeper cover and Nitish Reddy gets across and cuts it off
T Natarajan to Karthik, leg byes, 1 run, full and pitches outside the leg-stump, Karthik swings and misses, off the pad to fine-leg. T Natarajan and Karthik have a friendly chat
T Natarajan to Green, 1 run, low full-toss on the stumps, flicked to deep mid-wicket
T Natarajan [2.0-0-16-1] is back into the attack
Unadkat in IPL 2024 \nin Hyderabad: 12 overs | 6 wkt | Avg 17.66 | ER 8.83 \naway games: 9.1 overs | 1 wkt | Avg 119.00 | ER 12.98
Unadkat to Green, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter full outside off, Green reaches for it and drives to long-off
Unadkat to Green, FOUR, one hand came off the bat-handle but still the power does it, slower ball off-cutter dug in and Green pummels the pull wide of deep mid-wicket
Unadkat to Karthik, 1 run, just slower ball off-cutters now, full outside off, Karthik pushes wide of cover and is off the mark
Dinesh Karthik, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Unadkat to Lomror, out Caught by Cummins!! Third for Unadkat. The slower ball off-cutter is full outside off, Lomror tries to slogsweep to the deep mid-wicket stands, does not get the elevation and Cummins takes a good overhead catch. Never looked like dropping that despite being in an uncomfortable position. Unadkat looks at the heavens in appreciation. Lomror c Cummins b Unadkat 7(4) [4s-1]
Unadkat to Lomror, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Unadkat to Lomror, wide, the slower ball off-cutter is just wide of the tramline outside off and it's left alone to take the wide
Unadkat to Green, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, slugged to long-on

Unadkat to Green, 2 runs, tight 2nd and Klaasen disturbs the stumps before collecting the ball. A slower ball off-cutter on off, Green punches to sweeper cover and Shahbaz was the fielder, Green easily makes it back

Unadkat vs Kohli in IPL 59 balls 62 runs One dismissal SR 105.08 Among those who faced at least 30 balls off Unadkat in IPL, only Manish Pandey (89.74) & Ajinkya Rahane (100.00) have a lower SR against Unadkat than Kohli's 105.08.
Cummins to Lomror, FOUR, third boundary of the over. A slower ball off-cutter dug in short outside off, Lomror slashes and the ball flies over short third man
Cummins to Green, 1 run, full on the stumps, driven to long-on
Cummins to Green, FOUR, another slower ball off-cutter and it's again short on off, pulled wide of deep square leg, hit so hard that it gave Natarajan no chance
Phillips is on the field for Abhishek.
Cummins to Lomror, 1 run, tries the attempted yorker, it's a low full-toss following Lomror outside the leg-stump who drives to long-on
Cummins to Green, 1 run, full seam-up delivery outside off, drilled hard and straight to long-off
Cummins to Green, FOUR, nicely done. A slower ball off-cutter just outside off, Green pulls between long-on and deep mid-wicket, right into the gap
Pat Cummins [2.0-0-25-0] is back into the attack
Kohli innings progression today \nPowerplay: 32 off 18 (SR 177.78; 4 X 4s; 1 X 6s) \nMiddle overs: 19 off 25 (SR 76.00; No boundaries)
Unadkat to Lomror, 2 runs, slower ball full on the stumps, Lomror gets forward to loft straight down the ground for a couple
Mahipal Lomror, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Unadkat to Kohli, out Caught by Abdul Samad!! Straight to deep square leg. The slower ball off-cutter dug in on off, Kohli pulls but doesn't get the power and it's a comfortable catch. Unadkat is all smiles while the Tollywood star Victory Venkatesh is swirling the SRH flag in full excitement. Kohli tried to up the rate but he falls in the process. Kohli c Abdul Samad b Unadkat 51(43) [4s-4 6s-1]
Unadkat to Kohli, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Unadkat to Green, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter dug in outside off, pulled hard and straight to deep mid-wicket
Unadkat to Green, wide, slower ball off-cutter is down leg, Green flicks and misse

Unadkat to Kohli, leg byes, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter and angling into the pads, Kohli swipes and misses, impact outside the leg-stump, they take a legbye, Kohli slams the bat into the pad in frustration
Unadkat to Kohli, no run, looks like the message has reached Kohli. He goes for a big swipe across the line to a length delivery outside off, misses, swung away too from off-stump
Last four T20 innings at Hyderabad for Kohli 94*(50) vs WI 2019 63(48) vs Aus 2022 100(63) vs SRH 2023 51*(40) vs SRH 2024
Unadkat to Green, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter just outside off, Green punches to long-off

Highlights (Overs 7-14) -- 75/2 -- Markande knocks over Jacks for 6 -- Patidar takes flight as he smashes 19-ball fifty -- He hits four consecutive sixes off Markande -- Kohli slows down, fails to find the fence after powerplay -- Unadkat removes Patidar for 50 (12.4) -- Kohli brings up fifty off 37 balls

Timeout! RCB are in a good position but Kohli needs to up his strike-rate. He is nudging and prodding around. If not for Patidar's explosive knock, RCB would be well behind what they want to get against this monster SRH side.
Shahbaz Ahmed to Kohli, no run, so nearly chopped on. Tries to punch the flat good length delivery outside off, the thick inside-edge bounces past leg-stump and to Klaasen
Shahbaz Ahmed to Green, 1 run, wide of the crease and angling into Green on a good length on leg-stump, punched to long-on
Shahbaz Ahmed to Kohli, 1 run, slower and on a length outside off, punched in the air but on the bounce to long-off
Shahbaz Ahmed to Kohli, no run, fired full and wide outside off, Kohli misses the slogsweep and Klaasen whips the bails off, but Kohli has gone nowhere
Shahbaz Ahmed to Green, 1 run, flat good length on the stumps, Green punches to sweeper cover
Shahbaz Ahmed to Kohli, 1 run, 50 for Kohli. His superb run continues. Shortish outside off, flat-batted to long-off. No celebrations from Kohli at all
Shahbaz Ahmed [2.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
Unadkat to Kohli, 1 run, 103.7kph, pace off, Kohli works it to midwicket for a single
Unadkat to Green, 1 run, 131.4kph, pitched up delivery, Green gets off the mark by on-driving it to long-on
Cameron Green, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Unadkat to Rajat Patidar, out Caught by Abdul Samad!! Fifty and out! 130.4kph, low full toss on leg, Rajat Patidar whips it straight to deep square leg where Samad reverse-cups it. He made good contact but picked out the fielder in the deep. End of a superb knock from Patidar. Relief for SRH! Rajat Patidar c Abdul Samad b Unadkat 50(20) [4s-2 6s-5]
Unadkat to Rajat Patidar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Unadkat to Kohli, 1 run, 111.6kph, off-speed ball, Kohli shimmies down the track to punch it to long-off

Fastest 50s for RCB in IPL by balls faced 17 C Gayle vs PWI Bengaluru 2013 19 R Uthappa vs PK Bengaluru 2010 19 R Patidar vs SRH Hyderabad 2024 * 21 AB de Villiers vs RR Jaipur 2012 21 R Patidar vs KKR Kolkata 2024
Unadkat to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, 112.3kph, slower ball on a length, turned to midwicket. Back-to-back fifties for Rajat Patidar; gets there in just 19 deliveries!
Unadkat to Kohli, 1 run, off-speed back of a length ball, Kohli walks forward, flicks to midwicket and Kohli calls for two. Rajat Patidar rightly sends him back
Jaydev Unadkat [1.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
Cummins to Kohli, 1 run, 120.5kph, slower ball bouncer, pulled towards fine leg and Natarajan runs to his right to cut it off. Just six runs conceded by the captain after that massive over
Cummins to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, 104.8kph, slower ball that dips on the batter. A low full toss and Rajat Patidar bunts it to long-on
Cummins to Kohli, 1 run, 121.3kph, slow and short just outside off, Kohli pulls hard for a single. Deep midwicket takes it on the bounce
Cummins to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, 142.8kph, low full toss, wristed towards long-on
Cummins to Kohli, 1 run, back of a length, punched to the left of long-off who is quick to get across and throw the ball back to Cummins
Cummins to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, length ball outside off, cut hard to deep point
Pat Cummins [1.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack
Fifty partnership and here's Cummins...
Markande to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, 90.5kph, quicker one, Rajat Patidar nudges it to midwicket and keeps the strike. 27 runs off the over!
Rajat Patidar vs leg spin in IPL 88 balls 193 runs Avg 64.33 SR 219.31 4s/6s hit 6/20

Markande to Rajat Patidar, SIX, four sixes in a row! Looped up delivery well outside off at 73.5kph, Rajat Patidar goes after this one as well. Reaches out and lofts it handsomely over deep extra cover
Markande to Rajat Patidar, SIX, 83.2kph, googly and that's been walloped over deep midwicket! Stays in his crease and heaves it with the spin over deep midwicket. Stunning hit!

Markande to Rajat Patidar, SIX, middle-stump line and Rajat Patidar decides to loft downtown again. Didn't quite middle it but he's got enough wood on it. Markram moves to his right from long-off and waits for this high ball but it's out of his reach
Markande to Rajat Patidar, SIX, 86.5kph, tossed up and full delivery wide of off. Overpitched and Rajat Patidar gets forward to loft it over long-off for an 86m six
Markande to Rajat Patidar, wide, 80.4kph, tries to bowl outside Patidar's arc and ends up bowling too wide outside off, left alone
Markande to Kohli, 1 run, 84.2kph, tossed up, full in length, driven along the ground to long-off
Unadkat to Kohli, 1 run, short of length ball, tucked into the midwicket pocket

Unadkat to Kohli, 2 runs, 106.7kph, another slower ball to Kohli. The batter walks down the track and slaps through extra cover. Klassen covers a lot of distance running to his left from long-off and keeps the batters down to two
Unadkat to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, 130.2kph, pace on, Patidar looks to flick and gets a leading edge that goes to Bhuvi at short third man on the bounce who fails to collect it cleanly
Unadkat to Rajat Patidar, FOUR, 111.7kph, too predictable. Slower ball bouncer outside off, Rajat Patidar sees that coming. Waits for it and slams the pull over midwicket for a one-bounce four
Unadkat to Kohli, 1 run, 128.7kph, on the shorter side again, Kohli plays with soft hands to tap it towards short third man for a single
Unadkat to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, 112.6kph, slow and short from round the wicket, Patidar moves leg-side to pull it to deep midwicket
Jaydev Unadkat, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Strategic timeout! RCB, opting to bat, came out all guns blazing as they scored 43 off the first three overs. But SRH have pulled things back. Natarajan removed Faf and the spinners aren't offering too many freebies. Rajat Patidar is looking to be aggressive against the tweakers. Kohli, on the other hand, has got a start...
Markande to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, 87.7kph, leggie on a good length, uppishly driven towards long-off
Markande to Kohli, 1 run, 76.3kph, looped up outside off, Kohli sweeps hard but inside-halves it to deep midwicket
Markande to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, 87.5kph, flat on middle and leg, turned to midwicket
Markande to Kohli, 1 run, 88.4kph, full on the stumps, worked through backward square leg
Markande to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, 87.7kph, flatter and shorter, hurriedly pulled to long-on
Markande to Rajat Patidar, SIX, 84.5kph, tossed up, full in the slot, Patidar clears his front leg to pump it downtown. Powerful strike!

Shahbaz Ahmed to Kohli, no run, 94.5kph, half an appeal for lbw as Shahbaz Ahmed gets this slide on with the arm. Kohli misses the flick to get hit on the front pad but that's missing leg with the angle
Shahbaz Ahmed to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, 94.6kph, in-dart, heaved to deep midwicket who comes in and takes it on the bounce
Shahbaz Ahmed to Rajat Patidar, FOUR, 94.9kph, full marginally outside off, Patidar stays leg-side of the ball and swings hard to thump it over the bowler's head
Shahbaz Ahmed to Kohli, 1 run, 96.3kph, punched wide of cover, a slight misfield results in an easy single
Shahbaz Ahmed to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, 91.5kph, in-dart on off, knocked to long-off
Shahbaz Ahmed to Kohli, 1 run, 91.1kph, short of length, jabbed to long-on off the back foot
Shahbaz Ahmed [1.0-0-2-0] is back into the attack
Rajat Patidar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Spin from both ends now!

Markande to Will Jacks, out Bowled!! Cleaned up! Will Jacks kept swinging at everything and he perishes for a cheap score. A teasing tossed up ball from Markande, bowls it very slow and Jacks gets low to sweep across the line. It's the leggie that doesn't spin much and goes underneath the swingling blade of the batter before hitting the off-stump. Will Jacks b Markande 6(9)
Markande to Will Jacks, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!
Markande to Kohli, 1 run, 98.9kph, quicker one on off, Kohli stays back to drive it to long-off
Markande to Will Jacks, 1 run, 83.7kph, wrong 'un, punched to long-on off the back foot
Markande to Kohli, 1 run, 77.1kph, leggie on a short of length, flicked through midwicket off the back foot
Markande to Kohli, no run, 86.9kph, squeeze-driven to the left of the bowler and Markande is quick to get to the ball
Markande to Will Jacks, 1 run, 95.8kph, tossed up outside off, smashed to long-on for a single
Mayank Markande, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack

Powerplay summary -- RCB openers get off to a quick start -- Bhuvi goes for 14 in his first over -- Cummins goes for 19 in his first over -- Natarajan, Shahbaz put the brakes on -- Faf dismissed for 25 by Natarajan (3.5) -- Shahbaz concedes just two singles in his first over

T Natarajan to Will Jacks, 1 run, 120.9kph, pace off and short in length, Jacks miscues the pull and the ball goes to mid-on off the inner edge. Risky single taken and luckily for Jacks, there's no direct-hit at the bowler's end
T Natarajan to Kohli, 1 run, 132.6kph, full delivery on middle, knocked to long-on
T Natarajan to Kohli, no run, 121.3kph, pace off and shortened length, chopped to cover
T Natarajan to Kohli, SIX, 130.9kph, shot! Natarajan goes touch too full and Kohli pounces. Gets forward and hits through the line as he middle the lofted on-drive. Poses for the photographs as well!

T Natarajan to Will Jacks, 1 run, 132.5kph, length ball just outside off, Will Jacks backs away to slap it through the off-side, only manages to get an inside edge which takes the ball towards mid-off
T Natarajan to Kohli, 1 run, 133.7kph, back of a length, leg-lined, Kohli walks down the pitch to flick and inside-edges towards short fine leg for a sharp single

Shahbaz Ahmed to Will Jacks, no run, 95kph, full on the stumps, too full to be slogsweeping and Will Jacks luckily gets an inside edge. The ball rolls to short fine leg and Shahbaz has his hands on head. Just 2 runs off the over!
Shahbaz Ahmed to Kohli, 1 run, 98.6kph, quicker and shorter, Kohli makes room to punch it to long-off
Shahbaz Ahmed to Kohli, no run, 94.4kph, no toom on offer, Kohli nudges it into the leg-side
Shahbaz Ahmed to Kohli, no run, 92.9kph, off-stump line from a good length, Kohli rocks back and cuts straight to cover point
Shahbaz Ahmed to Will Jacks, 1 run, 82.5kph, Jacks shapes to slog across the line and inside-edges through midwicket for a single
Shahbaz Ahmed to Will Jacks, no run, 96.4kph, in-drifter on the stumps, driven back to the bowler off the inner part of the bat
Shahbaz Ahmed, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
T Natarajan to Will Jacks, 1 run, 136.6kph, pitched up outside off, driven through point
Will Jacks, right handed bat, comes to the crease

T Natarajan to du Plessis, out Caught by Markram!! Natarajan strikes! Dug in short outside off, du Plessis moves leg-side to try and go over the infield (covers). He actually shadow-practised this after the previous ball. However, the ball comes slower than he expects and that results in a miscue. Markram backpedals from mid-off and moves to his left to catch it calmly. SRH get the breakthrough! du Plessis c Markram b T Natarajan 25(12) [4s-3 6s-1]
T Natarajan to du Plessis, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
T Natarajan to du Plessis, no run, 121.5kph, slower ball into the deck, du Plessis stays leg-side and toe-ends the slap to extra cover
T Natarajan to du Plessis, no run, 135kph, overpitched on middle, du Plessis drills it down the ground and Natarajan uses his left boot to deflect it to mid-off
T Natarajan to Kohli, 1 run, 119.7kph, pace off and on a length, tapped in front of point for a quick single
T Natarajan to Kohli, FOUR, 133.5kph, I0$ Half-volley on the pads and Kohli whips it between mid-on and midwicket. Speeds away to the fence
T Natarajan, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Fourth over, fourth bowler!

Cummins to du Plessis, 2 runs, 139.8kph, the line is too straight from Cummins and du Plessis pulls through backward square leg. Once again, Natarajan has to run to his left to mop it up. 19 runs off Cummins's opening over!

Cummins to du Plessis, 2 runs, 120.6kph, slower ball into the wicket, pulled to the left of fine leg. Natarajan runs across and somehow manages to stop it. Over-runs and then gets back to throw the ball

Cummins to du Plessis, SIX, 141.8kph, fuller than a length on the stumps, du Plessis walks across to get inside the line, gets down on one leg and uses the bowler's pace and angle to scoop it over fine leg. Very good contact and it's gone all the way
Cummins to Kohli, 1 run, 142.8kph, full and angled in, clipped away to deep midwicket
Cummins to Kohli, FOUR, 140.3kph, short of a length ball outside off, Kohl stands tall to punch it aerially over extra cover for a one-bounce four. A stylish shot from Kohli!
Cummins to Kohli, FOUR, Kohli greets Cummins with a boundary! There's the intent. Shimmies down the track to this seam-up ball and brings his wrists into play to whip it over midwicket
Pat Cummins, right-arm fast, comes into the attack

Bhuvneshwar to du Plessis, FOUR, 121.2kph, no need to chase this! Bhuvneshwar serves width after pulling his length back and that's been slapped through extra cover by the RCB captain. A cracking shot. 14 runs off the over

Bhuvneshwar to du Plessis, FOUR, 122.1kph, pace off and full outside off. Faf du Plessis is early into his shot. Moves leg-side and tries to go over the on-side. Goes much squarer and beats Samad's chase
Bhuvneshwar to Kohli, 1 run, 135.8kph, back of a length outside off, Kohli walks forward to punch it to deep point
Bhuvneshwar to Kohli, no run, 135.9kph, inswinger, no room on offer and Kohli defends it back to the bowler
A wide slip for Kohli
Bhuvneshwar to du Plessis, 1 run, 133.3kph, short of a good length ball around off, pushed towards mid-off for a quick single

Bhuvneshwar to du Plessis, FOUR, 129.6kph, short of length delivery outside off, du Plessis stands tall on the back foot and punches through the covers. Nitish gives a chase, dives and tries to flick it back but to no avail
Bhuvneshwar Kumar, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Can Bhuvi find some swing? A slip in place
Abhishek Sharma to Kohli, 2 runs, 96.8kph, full toss, flicked through midwicket. 10 runs off the opening over!
Abhishek Sharma to du Plessis, 1 run, 88.2kph, driven hard to the left of the bowler and Abhishek could only half-stop it with his left hand
Abhishek Sharma to Kohli, 1 run, 88.5kph, shortened length, wristily pulled to deep midwicket
Abhishek Sharma to du Plessis, 1 run, 89.8kph, bit of flight, full on the stumps, du Plessis stays leg-side and drives to the left of long-off
Abhishek Sharma to Kohli, 1 run, 94.1kph, full on off, driven along the ground to long-off

Abhishek Sharma to Kohli, FOUR, Kohli and RCB are underway! 100.1kph, bit of inswing but the line is too straight. Pad-lined, Kohli flicks through backward square leg to get off the mark with a boundary
Kohli and du Plessis are at the crease. Kohli is on strike. Abhishek Sharma will open the attack
